<title>Signed, Sealed, Delivered: UK Subscription Service Sends Whiskey in a Pouch</title>
<link>https://www.geek.com/culture/signed-sealed-delivered-uk-subscription-service-sends-whiskey-in-a-pouch-1722296/?source</link>
<guid isPermaLink="true" >https://www.geek.com/culture/signed-sealed-delivered-uk-subscription-service-sends-whiskey-in-a-pouch-1722296/?source</guid>
<description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Whiskey is a pricey, time-consuming hobby, which can leave newbies drowning in distilled alcohol.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&amp;#13;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The owners of London’s &lt;a href=&quot;http://blackrock.bar&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;Black Rock&lt;/a&gt; whiskey bar want to simplify the process with a new subscription service, &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.whisky-me.com/&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;Whiskey Me&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&amp;#13;
&amp;#13;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;UK-based members receive different drams each month, packaged in 5 cL (50 mL) pouches (think boozy Capri Sun), thin enough to fit through the letterbox—no signature required.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&amp;#13;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;“Inside the pouch is a whisky that’s been hand-selected by our tasting panel to best represent the glorious flavors and diversity of single malt whisky,” according to the company website.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&amp;#13;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Distilled from fermented mash made exclusively with malted barley, single malts are typically associated with Scotch (i.e. made in Scotland), but are also produced in other countries.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&amp;#13;
&amp;#13;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;iframe width=&quot;500&quot; height=&quot;281&quot; src=&quot;https://www.youtube.com/embed/HcBUG3r3Jhw?feature=oembed?wmode=transparent&quot; frameborder=&quot;0&quot; gesture=&quot;media&quot; allowfullscreen=&quot;&quot;&gt;[embedded content]&lt;/iframe&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&amp;#13;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;November’s pick is a Speyside single malt from The Macallan distillery in Moray, Scotland. Described as “liquid sunlight matured in a sherry cask,” the &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.themacallan.com/the-whisky/fine-oak/12-years-old&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;12-year-old Macallan ‘Fine Oak’&lt;/a&gt; boasts hints of fruit and honey, oak and spice, and a touch of vanilla.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&amp;#13;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Shipped out on the first Tuesday of the month, subscribers should receive their first pouch in time for the weekend. (“Not that whisky drinking should be limited to weekends,” the firm is quick to point out.)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&amp;#13;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Whisky Me is the brainchild of Black Rock founders Tom Aske and Tristan Stephenson, who have put an interesting twist on Bottle of the Month services.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&amp;#13;
&amp;#13;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Each pouch not only contains a distinct taste, but also provides “simple, useful explanations of what you’re drinking.” Plus, members receive exclusive aerial HD drone footage and distillery data.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&amp;#13;
&lt;div id=&quot;attachment_1722297&quot; class=&quot;wp-caption alignnone&quot; readability=&quot;32&quot;&gt;&lt;img class=&quot;size-full wp-image-1722297&quot; src=&quot;https://www.geek.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/11/whisky-2.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;690&quot; height=&quot;388&quot; srcset=&quot;https://www.geek.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/11/whisky-2.jpg 690w, https://www.geek.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/11/whisky-2-300x169.jpg 300w, https://www.geek.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/11/whisky-2-625x352.jpg 625w, https://www.geek.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/11/whisky-2-650x366.jpg 650w, https://www.geek.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/11/whisky-2-141x80.jpg 141w, https://www.geek.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/11/whisky-2-130x73.jpg 130w&quot; sizes=&quot;(max-width: 690px) 100vw, 690px&quot;/&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;wp-caption-text&quot;&gt;The subscription service is currently available only in the UK (via Whisky Me)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&amp;#13;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;“Wouldn’t it be great if everyone—okay, everyone in the UK (for now)—could appreciate the rich diversity of single malt whisky, with minimal fuss and minimal cost, one large glass at a time?” the website said.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&amp;#13;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The startup currently counts 139 active members. Like a crowdfunding campaign, though, Whisky Me offers stretch goals, promising a free pouch of “table whisky” from Black Rock once it reaches 500 subscribers.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&amp;#13;
&amp;#13;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;“The Black Rock house whisky blend is ‘finished’ in an 18-foot English oak tree trunk. When we hit 500 subscribers, we’ll send every member a free pouch with their normal monthly delivery,” according to the firm.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&amp;#13;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Additional milestones will follow. Fingers crossed that one of them is international shipping to the US.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&amp;#13;
&amp;#13;
&amp;#13;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Let us know what you like about Geek by &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.research.net/r/geeksocnps&quot;&gt;taking our survey&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&amp;#13;
</description>
<pubDate>Fri, 10 Nov 2017 19:15:14 +0000</pubDate>
<dc:creator>Stephanie Mlot</dc:creator>
