<title>Hidden Valley Busts Out a 5-liter Ranch Keg for the Holidays</title>
<link>https://www.geek.com/culture/hidden-valley-busts-out-a-5-liter-ranch-keg-for-the-holidays-1722317/?source</link>
<guid isPermaLink="true" >https://www.geek.com/culture/hidden-valley-busts-out-a-5-liter-ranch-keg-for-the-holidays-1722317/?source</guid>
<description>&lt;div class=&quot;figure&quot;&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAIBRAA7&quot; data-src=&quot;[https://www.geek.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/11/ranch-keg-650x366.jpg,(default)],[https://www.geek.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/11/ranch-keg-625x352.jpg,(small)]&quot; width=&quot;650&quot; height=&quot;366&quot;/&gt;&lt;noscript&gt;&amp;#13;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;https://www.geek.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/11/ranch-keg-650x366.jpg&quot; width=&quot;650&quot; height=&quot;366&quot;/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&amp;#13;
&lt;/noscript&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;article readability=&quot;43.643702906351&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;Holiday party season is upon us, Geek readers! That means it’s time to bust out the apps and cut up the crudités… Oh, and make sure you have plenty of delicious dip on hand for your fellow partygoers.&lt;/p&gt;&amp;#13;
&lt;p&gt;Ranch dressing is a versatile (and extremely popular) option. Typically, though, you’d buy it a bottle or two at a time. Why do that and risk running out at a critical point in the merrymaking? Hidden Valley has a better option.&lt;/p&gt;&amp;#13;
&amp;#13;
&lt;p&gt;Behold: the &lt;a href=&quot;http://digg.com/2017/one-keg-full-of-ranch&quot;&gt;ranch keg&lt;/a&gt;! This shining metal behemoth stands 10 inches high, has a six-inch diameter, and holds five glorious liters of Hidden Valley’s signature dressing inside. That should be more than enough to get you, your co-workers, and neighbors through the holiday season. Heck, there should even be enough left over to cover your Super Bowl party come February.&lt;/p&gt;&amp;#13;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.flavourgallery.com/collections/hidden-valley-ranch/products/hidden-valley-ranch-keg&quot;&gt;Flavor Gallery’s online shop&lt;/a&gt; says it’s enough Hidden Valley to last you an entire year. At the bargain price of just $50, I’m guessing they have a long line of customers waiting to put that claim to the test. We should probably brace ourselves for a spate of “ranch dressing challenge” videos on YouTube.&lt;/p&gt;&amp;#13;
&lt;p&gt;As is often the case with buzzworthy bizarre items for sale on the Internet, Flavor Gallery has been swamped with orders and they won’t be shipping any more of these bad boys until December 20. Sadly that means it’s too late for Hanukkah m but they should still be able to hook you up in time for Christmas, Boxing Day, Kwanzaa, and New Year’s.&lt;/p&gt;&amp;#13;
&amp;#13;
&lt;p&gt;One piece of advice before we wrap up. For those of you who decide to deploy the 5L Hidden Valley keg, please keep it a safe distance away from any &lt;em&gt;other&lt;/em&gt; kegs you may have set up for your guests to enjoy. The last thing you’d want to deal with in the middle of a party is the aftermath of an unfortunate ranch kegstand.&lt;/p&gt;&amp;#13;
&amp;#13;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Let us know what you like about Geek by &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.research.net/r/geeksocnps&quot;&gt;taking our survey&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&amp;#13;
