<title>Take Christmas Dinner to the Next Level With Christmas Cake Pepsi</title>
<link>https://www.geek.com/culture/take-christmas-dinner-to-the-next-level-with-christmas-cake-pepsi-1722155/?source</link>
<guid isPermaLink="true" >https://www.geek.com/culture/take-christmas-dinner-to-the-next-level-with-christmas-cake-pepsi-1722155/?source</guid>
<description>&lt;div class=&quot;figure&quot;&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAIBRAA7&quot; data-src=&quot;[https://www.geek.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/11/xmascola-650x366.png,(default)],[https://www.geek.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/11/xmascola-625x352.png,(small)]&quot; width=&quot;650&quot; height=&quot;366&quot;/&gt;&lt;noscript&gt;&amp;#13;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;https://www.geek.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/11/xmascola-650x366.png&quot; width=&quot;650&quot; height=&quot;366&quot;/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&amp;#13;
&lt;/noscript&gt;
&lt;p&gt;via SoraNews24&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;article readability=&quot;38.872340425532&quot;&gt;&amp;#13;
&lt;p&gt;Santa typically chows down on cookies on Christmas Eve and slurps on some white milk as well, but what if you had some delicious Christmas cake Pepsi to leave out for jolly ol’ St. Nick? That’s exactly what Japanese Pepsi fans will be able to do this year, with &lt;a href=&quot;https://en.rocketnews24.com/2017/11/09/christmas-cake-flavored-pepsi-is-set-to-make-the-holidays-a-little-sweeter-in-japan/&quot;&gt;Christmas Cake Pepsi&lt;/a&gt;, coming just in time for the holidays. Yes, this is a Christmas cake you can drink…if you’ve ever wanted to do that.&lt;/p&gt;&amp;#13;
&lt;p&gt;The Christmas Pepsi has a very interesting flavor profile, and one you’re probably not expecting from soda. Christmas Cake, to start with, is a strawberry shortcake. It’s an important part of the holidays, and it’s called a Christmas Cake because of it. So technically this soda is a strawberry and cream soda, which sounds pretty delicious, to be honest. It may look a little suspect, but it might taste a little something like mixing strawberry soda with cream, and that might be pretty delicious.&lt;/p&gt;&amp;#13;
&amp;#13;
&lt;p&gt;If you’ve never tasted any differently-flavored Pepsis, you might be taken aback by its flavor, but it seems as though it might taste a little like Cool Whip or Barq’s Cream Soda with strawberry syrup poured in. You’d be forgiven for being a bit apprehensive of the beverage, especially since it looks pretty cloudy and strange, but it might end up tasting just like the holidays…if strawberry shortcake is something that you equate with the holidays or Christmas, after all.&lt;/p&gt;&amp;#13;
&lt;p&gt;Pepsi Christmas Cola is supposed to go on sale on November 21, right around when we’re going to celebrate Thanksgiving in America. Since that’s not so much a thing in Japan, it makes sense that the country needs something a little delicious and refreshing to tide them over until Christmas and the rest of the holidays, where savory KFC-branded fried chicken is available in droves.&lt;/p&gt;&amp;#13;
&amp;#13;
&amp;#13;
